                            <comment id="12780269" author="junrao" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2009 21:19:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attach a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12780272" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2009 21:27:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you add a test illustrating the bug?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12780274" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2009 21:30:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;since the contract for RandomAccessFile that BRAF is patterned on is that read() may return less bytes even if it is not EOF, IMO we should probably make the read-with-retry loop a separate method (readFully?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12780288" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2009 21:49:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(now that I see that this is documented behavior I withdraw the request for a test)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12780297" author="junrao" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2009 22:06:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch v2. Use the existing readFully method in CommitLog instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12780298" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2009 22:12:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12780304" author="junrao" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2009 22:26:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed to trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12780538" author="hudson" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2009 12:35:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #264 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/264/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/264/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
